# Design System Package - AI Assistant Prompts

## Quick Reference for AI Assistants

This design system package provides React components built with shadcn/ui, Radix UI, and Tailwind CSS.

## Installation & Setup

```bash
npm install @your-username/design-system
npm install react react-dom tailwindcss @tailwindcss/postcss
```

**Import styles in your CSS:**
```css
@import "@your-username/design-system/styles";
@import "tailwindcss";
```

## Using Components

### Basic Import Pattern

```tsx
import { Button, Card, Input } from '@your-username/design-system'
```

### Available Components

**UI Components:**
- Button, Input, Label, Card, Select, Tabs, Switch
- Dialog, Dropdown Menu, Table, Tooltip, Sheet, Toast (Sonner)

**Custom Components:**
- Skeleton (feedback)
- AutocompleteInput, CostComparisonCard, AlertSubscriptionCard (forms)
- ShareBlock (sharing)
- PriceCard, WeatherCard, NDVICard (data-display)
- CompareGate, CompareResult (comparison)
- PageHeader, HeroSection (layout)

## Design Tokens

**ALWAYS use design tokens, NEVER hardcoded values:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use tokens
<Button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
  Click me
</Button>

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
<Button className="bg-[#2406%] text-white">
  Click me
</Button>
```

### Available Token Classes

- Colors: `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, `bg-accent`, `bg-success`, `bg-warning`, `bg-danger`, `bg-info`
- Radius: `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`
- Borders: `border-border`
- Backgrounds: `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-muted`

## Component Patterns

### Button Example

```tsx
import { Button } from '@your-username/design-system'

// Variants: default, destructive, outline, secondary, ghost, link
// Sizes: default, sm, lg, icon

<Button variant="default" size="default">Click me</Button>
<Button variant="destructive" size="sm">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="outline">Cancel</Button>
```

### Card Example

```tsx
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from '@your-username/design-system'

<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    Content here
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

### Form Example

```tsx
import { Input, Label, Button } from '@your-username/design-system'

<div className="space-y-2">
  <Label htmlFor="email">Email</Label>
  <Input id="email" type="email" placeholder="Enter email" />
  <Button type="submit">Submit</Button>
</div>
```

