## Common Patterns

### Creating a Form

```tsx
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from '@your-username/design-system'
import { Input, Label, Button } from '@your-username/design-system'

export function MyForm() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Form Title</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent className="space-y-4">
        <div className="space-y-2">
          <Label htmlFor="name">Name</Label>
          <Input id="name" />
        </div>
        <Button type="submit">Submit</Button>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

### Using Custom Components

```tsx
import { PriceCard, WeatherCard, Skeleton } from '@your-username/design-system'

// PriceCard example
<PriceCard 
  title="Product Name"
  price={99.99}
  currency="USD"
/>

// WeatherCard example
<WeatherCard 
  location="New York"
  temperature={72}
  condition="sunny"
/>

// Skeleton loading
<Skeleton className="h-4 w-full" />
```

## TypeScript Support

All components are fully typed. Use TypeScript for better autocomplete:

```tsx
import type { ButtonProps } from '@your-username/design-system'

const MyButton: React.FC<ButtonProps> = (props) => {
  return <Button {...props} />
}
```

## Styling Guidelines

1. **Use design tokens** - Never hardcode colors, spacing, or radius
2. **Use Tailwind utilities** - Classes like `space-y-4`, `flex`, `grid`
3. **Follow component variants** - Use built-in variants before custom styling
4. **Maintain consistency** - Follow patterns from existing components

## Troubleshooting

**Styles not working?**
- Ensure you've imported the styles: `@import "@your-username/design-system/styles"`
- Make sure Tailwind CSS is configured in your project

**Components not found?**
- Check package installation: `npm list @your-username/design-system`
- Verify import path matches package exports

**Type errors?**
- Ensure React types are installed: `npm install @types/react @types/react-dom`
- Check TypeScript version compatibility

